<div class="b_title">Auditor Graduate Course</div>



<p class="marginBtm50">On June 4, 2021, GPC signed a business agreement with the Korean Standards Association (KSA) for the operation and overall qualification management of the “Auditor Graduate Course (AGC)”. The signing ceremony was attended by Gong Woo-joo, vice president of GPC and Park Jin-seong, executive of the Certification Division of KSA.</p>


<p class="img_box" style="width:60%;"><img src="/gpc_eng/theme/gpcert/info/images/thumb-nt_content2_img1_835x527.png" title="AGC" alt="Auditor Graduate Course"></p>



<p class="marginBtm06">Through the business agreement, GPC and KSA promised mutual cooperation for the objective verification of the competence of auditors in the “AGC”.</p>

<p class="marginBtm06">The “AGC” is operated for qualified ISO 9001 provisional auditors who aim to acquire ISO 9001 certification auditor, and consists of audit theory and practice training and competence verification evaluation.</p>

<p class="marginBtm30">If the competence evaluation is passed, ISO certification auditor qualification can be acquired.</p>

Currently there is only for the ISO 9001 standard, and it will be expanded to other ISO standards in the future.

